# DevOps Rules — Harness Engineering

## Core Principles
- Infrastructure as Code is preferred.
- All deployments must go through CI/CD pipelines.
- Observability must be considered in every meaningful change.
- Changes to infrastructure or pipelines require explicit approval.

## Hard Stops
- Never run production deployment commands (`terraform apply`, `helm upgrade`, etc.) without explicit user approval.
- Never modify CI/CD pipeline files without a plan and approval.
- Never push directly to production branches.
- Never auto-install or upgrade infrastructure tools.

## Recommended Practices
- Use feature branches for all infrastructure changes.
- Include observability updates in every relevant plan.
- Document deployment steps in `docs/`.
- Prefer GitOps (declarative) approaches.

Follow these rules in addition to `harness-engineering.mdc`.